<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-18T17:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-18T17:41:00-05:00" n="627" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d627">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/10–1851: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the United States</hi> (<gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">GATT</hi></gloss>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-18T17:41:00-05:00">October
                                    18, 1951—5:41 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Gatt 104. House Banking and Currency Comite has scheduled hearings Oct 19
                            on repeal Sec 104. Thorp and McCormick, <gloss target="#t_Agric1">Agric</gloss>, will testify. Efforts continuing to get Senate
                            action. House hearings may help in getting Senate action.</p>
                        <p>Congress, however, pushing for adjournment by night October 19. If
                            Congress adjourns, then, chances getting repeal Sec 104 practically nil.
                            If it does not, we still have fighting chance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>